---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="Terms that govern access to the Gruntz mobile app, paid membership, and use of the website at gruntzfit.com."
  kicker="Terms of Use"
>
  <p>
    These Terms of Use govern your use of the Gruntz mobile app, the website at {site.domain}, and
    related support pages. By using the app or this website, you agree to these terms.
  </p>

  <div class="callout">
    Effective date: {site.updated}. Support contact: <a href={`mailto:${site.supportEmail}`}>{site.supportEmail}</a>.
  </div>

  <h2>1. Product Scope</h2>
  <p>
    Gruntz is a fitness product designed to present tactical-style training missions, workout
    references, progress metrics, and subscription-managed premium access. The product is intended
    for training guidance and self-directed fitness use.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Not Medical Advice</h2>
  <p>
    Gruntz does not provide medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. You are responsible for
    determining whether any workout, mission, or training plan is appropriate for your condition,
    skill level, and health status. Stop training and consult a qualified professional if you have
    pain, injury concerns, or medical questions.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Eligibility and Safe Use</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You are responsible for using the app safely and within your own limits.</li>
    <li>You should follow local laws and safety rules when running, rucking, or training outdoors.</li>
    <li>You are responsible for the accuracy of any information you choose to enter into the app.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Membership, Trial Access, and Billing</h2>
  <p>
    The current Gruntz launch model includes a {site.trialDays}-day app-level access window for new
    users, followed by a premium membership path through Gruntz Pro at {site.price}.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Subscription availability, billing, renewal, and cancellation are handled by the app store.</li>
    <li>
      If you subscribe through Apple App Store or Google Play, those store rules control billing,
      renewals, cancellations, and refunds.
    </li>
    <li>We may change pricing, trial structure, or package availability in a future release.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. License and Acceptable Use</h2>
  <p>
    Subject to these terms, you receive a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use
    Gruntz for personal, non-commercial use.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>You may not reverse engineer, redistribute, resell, or exploit the app except as allowed by law.</li>
    <li>You may not use the service to violate laws, abuse payment systems, or harm other users.</li>
    <li>You may not remove branding, copyright notices, or legal notices from the product.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
  <p>
    The Gruntz name, branding, app design, training structure, copy, and related content remain the
    property of their respective owner unless otherwise stated. These terms do not transfer
    ownership of the product or website content to you.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    The app may rely on third-party providers such as RevenueCat, Apple App Store, and Google Play
    for billing, entitlement, and platform-managed purchase flows. Your use of those services may
    also be governed by their own policies and agreements.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Availability and Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may modify, suspend, or discontinue features, content, pricing, or product functionality at
    any time. We may also update these Terms of Use by posting a revised version on this site with a
    new effective date.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Disclaimers</h2>
  <p>
    Gruntz and this website are provided on an “as is” and “as available” basis to the fullest
    extent allowed by law. We do not guarantee uninterrupted availability, error-free operation, or
    specific training results.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the fullest extent permitted by law, we are not liable for indirect, incidental, special,
    consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of Gruntz, including training injuries,
    lost data, device issues, subscription disputes handled by the app stores, or downtime.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Termination</h2>
  <p>
    We may limit or terminate access to the website or app if use violates these terms, harms the
    service, or creates legal or operational risk.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these terms or billing-related support can be sent to
    <a href={`mailto:${site.supportEmail}`}>{site.supportEmail}</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
